WEBVTT

00:07:29.815 --> 00:07:32.156
and emphasizing them
is definitely more productive

00:07:32.180 --> 00:07:33.910
than working on weaknesses alone.

00:07:34.379 --> 00:07:38.398
But for a while now, I've been concerned
about the opposite problem.

00:07:38.927 --> 00:07:41.847
Remember what the powerlifting champ
Michael Hartle said:

00:07:41.871 --> 00:07:45.370
you can actually overdevelop one muscle
at the expense of another.

00:07:45.832 --> 00:07:47.298
You need some balance.

00:07:48.411 --> 00:07:52.753
At work, research shows it's common
for managers to overuse their strengths:

00:07:53.402 --> 00:07:56.228
the persuasive boss
who talks so forcefully

00:07:56.252 --> 00:07:59.052
that everyone else
in the room is silenced;

00:07:59.691 --> 00:08:02.372
the creative colleague,
who's still generating new ideas